* Information of a remote user of {@link MediaSession} or {@link MediaBrowserService}. * This can be used to decide whether the remote user is trusted app, and also differentiate * caller of {@link MediaSession} and {@link MediaBrowserService} callbacks. *

* See {@link #equals(Object)} to take a look at how it differentiate media controller. * * @see #isTrustedForMediaControl(RemoteUserInfo)

methods.name: public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
methods.comment:
* Returns equality of two RemoteUserInfo. Two RemoteUserInfo objects are equal
         * if and only if they have the same package name, same pid, and same uid.
         *
         * @param obj the reference object with which to compare.
         * @return {@code true} if equals, {@code false} otherwise
